This paper involves the use of autonomous unmanned aircraft and deep reinforcement learning for monitoring wildfires, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of deep reinforcement learning also suggests that it could fall under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also mentions the use of sensor information and mapping, which could fall under computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper's focus on developing and testing algorithms suggests that it could also fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
